# Celonis MCP Client Configuration Template
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual credentials

# ============================================
# AUTHENTICATION (Required - choose one)
# ============================================

# Option 1: OAuth2 Client Credentials (Recommended)
CELONIS_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id-here
CELONIS_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret-here

# Option 2: Legacy API Key (Not recommended)
# CELONIS_API_KEY=your-api-key-here

# ============================================
# MCP SERVER ENDPOINT (Required)
# ============================================

# Full MCP Server URL (Recommended)
CELONIS_ENDPOINT_URL=https://your-team.celonis.cloud/studio-copilot/api/v1/mcp-servers/mcp/your-asset-id

# OR: Separate Team URL and Server ID
# CELONIS_TEAM_URL=https://your-team.celonis.cloud
# CELONIS_SERVER_ID=your-asset-id

# ============================================
# ENVIRONMENT VARIABLE MAPPING
# ============================================
#
# The celonis_mcp.py script reads these variables in this order:
#
# 1. Command-line arguments (highest priority)
# 2. Environment variables from .env file (if not in CLI)
# 3. Error if neither provided
#
# Variable Usage in celonis_mcp.py:
# - CELONIS_CLIENT_ID     → Used in OAuth2 authentication flow
# - CELONIS_CLIENT_SECRET → Used in OAuth2 authentication flow
# - CELONIS_API_KEY       → Used for legacy authentication (if OAuth2 not provided)
# - CELONIS_ENDPOINT_URL  → Used as the MCP server endpoint
# - CELONIS_TEAM_URL      → Used to construct endpoint if ENDPOINT_URL not provided
# - CELONIS_SERVER_ID     → Used to construct endpoint if ENDPOINT_URL not provided
#
# Code Location: Lines 290-320 in celonis_mcp.py
# Loading Method: python-dotenv library (automatically loads .env file)
